        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;American Opportunity Accounts Act&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill establishes tax-exempt American Opportunity Accounts to provide children at birth with a $1,000 savings account with annual contributions up to $2,000 depending on family income. The accounts are available to children at age 18 for specified purposes, including educational expenses, home ownership, and investment that provides long-term returns.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
